      },
      "date": "2012-05-30 21:31:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 16: (2 inline comments)\n\nOleg, this patch _has_ been tested at LLNL, according to comments in LU-1282.  The earlier version had a problem with memory allocation under spinlocks, which was the reason for change #12.  All the later versions were resubmitted for intermittent test failures and rebasing.\n\nNote that this patch is not changing the behaviour of the stats, just avoiding extra allocations that are never used.  A more drastic patch might disable per-cpu stats for clients entirely, but it isn't clear that this would be good for fat SMP clients.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 16
    },
